<event wordnetid="100029378" confidence="0.8">
<action wordnetid="100037396" confidence="0.8">
<part wordnetid="113809207" confidence="0.8">
<act wordnetid="100030358" confidence="0.8">
<psychological_feature wordnetid="100023100" confidence="0.8">
<activity wordnetid="100407535" confidence="0.8">
<introduction wordnetid="100238022" confidence="0.8">
<language_unit wordnetid="106284225" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../720/568720.xml">
The Adventures of Wild Bill Hickok</link></language_unit>
</introduction>
</activity>
</psychological_feature>
</act>
</part>
</action>
</event>
</diversion>
</change_of_state>
</morpheme>
</ending>
</entertainment>
</show>
</change>
</beginning>
</it>, which Devine and Madison reprised on television.  He appeared over 75 times on <person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<presenter wordnetid="110466387" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../587/82587.xml">
Jack Benny</link></presenter>
</person>
's radio show between 1936 and 1942, often appearing in Benny's semi-regular western series of sketches "Buck Benny Rides Again".  </p>
<p>

And Devine worked in television.  He played "Hap" on the TV series <it><series wordnetid="108457976" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../165/1660165.xml">
Flipper</link></series>
</it> and hosted a children's TV show, <it><link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../578/160578.xml">
Andy's Gang</link></it>.  He starred in a <it><series wordnetid="108457976" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../389/1409389.xml">
Twilight Zone</link></series>
</it> episode as "Frisby", a talkative fibster faced with an alien invasion called "<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../249/3074249.xml">
Hocus-Pocus and Frisby</link>".  He was also a frequent guest star in many television shows throughout the 1950s and 1960s. </p>
<p>

Finally, Devine performed voice parts in <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../593/593.xml">
animated film</link>s, including "<fictional_character wordnetid="109587565" confidence="0.8">
<imaginary_being wordnetid="109483738" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../981/18833981.xml">
Friar Tuck</link></imaginary_being>
</fictional_character>
" in <person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<film_maker wordnetid="110088390" confidence="0.9173553029164789">
<actor wordnetid="109765278" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../917/32917.xml">
Disney's</link></actor>
</film_maker>
</person>
 <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../180/982180.xml">
Robin Hood</link></movie>
</it>. He provided the voice of Cornelius the Rooster in several <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../895/181895.xml">
Kellogg's Corn Flakes</link> TV commercials.</p>
<p>

